  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoring ecosystems creates a world of abundance and provides humanity with hope for a better future. Ecosystem Restoration Camps (ERC) is a global, grassroots movement that is restoring degraded ecosystems globally. Our 41 Ecosystem Restoration Projects (we call them Camps) have already planted 1,225,000 trees in our first 3 years and are currently restoring 4,392 Ha. Our big goal is to have one million people come together by 2030 and restore degraded ecosystems in 100 Camps around the world.</narrative>
  </description>
